claim.claim-text:
1. A saddle riding vehicle comprising: 
a vehicle body frame having a front and rear portion; 
an engine mounted at a center of the vehicle body frame; 
a saddle seat provided above the engine; 
rear wheels mounted on both sides of the rear portion of the vehicle body frame; 
a propeller shaft and a final speed reducer for transmitting power of the engine to the rear wheels, the propeller shaft being disposed with a rising gradient from the engine toward the final speed reducer; and 
a universal joint connecting the propeller shaft and an output shaft.

5. A four wheel vehicle comprising: 
a vehicle body frame having a front and rear portion; 
an engine mounted at a center of the vehicle body frame; 
a saddle seat provided above the engine; 
rear wheels mounted on both sides of the rear portion of the vehicle body frame; 
a propeller shaft and a final speed reducer for transmitting power of the engine to the rear wheels, the propeller shaft being disposed on a rising gradient from the engine toward the final speed reducer; 
a velocity ball joint connecting the propeller shaft and output shaft; and 
a left and a right drive shaft connected to the rear wheels, the left and right drive shafts having generally equal lengths with the final speed reducer being disposed at the center of the vehicle.
